</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBEABDD9FF95FFE939E60A3C4399BA9B" pageId="27" pageNumber="254" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FF95FFE939E60A3C4399BA9B" blockId="27.[136,1452,158,977]" pageId="27" pageNumber="254">
The specimen indicated by 
<bibRefCitation id="C76193A3FF95FFE938A80A3C4586BA0A" author="Martins, E. M. O." box="[499,680,266,293]" pageId="27" pageNumber="254" pagination="89 - 94" refId="ref43125" refString="Martins, E. M. O. (1975 a) Especies novas de Stryphnodendron para a flora do Brasil. Leandra 5 (6): 89 - 94." type="journal article" year="1975">Martins (1975a)</bibRefCitation>
as the 
<typeStatus id="7C4B50F0FF95FFE93BA30A3D4406BA0A" box="[760,808,267,293]" pageId="27" pageNumber="254">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FF95FFE93A140A3D434FBA0B" authority="A. Ducke" authorityName="A. Ducke" box="[847,1121,266,293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="27" pageNumber="254" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rizzinianum">
<emphasis id="91843240FF95FFE93A140A3D44C1BA0B" box="[847,1007,267,293]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="254">S. rizzinianum</emphasis>
A. Ducke
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="91843240FF95FFE93D330A3D43A1BA0B" box="[1128,1167,267,292]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="254">s.n.</emphasis>
(
<date id="D74EC892FF95FFE93DC50A3C420ABA0A" box="[1182,1316,266,293]" pageId="27" pageNumber="254" value="1935-11-07">07/XI/1935</date>
, RB 29044) has two different collection dates on the label, one referring to the flowering (
<date id="D74EC892FF95FFE93ABF0A184349BA66" box="[996,1127,302,329]" pageId="27" pageNumber="254" value="1935-11-07">07/XI/1935</date>
) and the other, to the fruiting (05/IV/36) sample, as frequently seen in Ducke´s gatherings. The name is validly published only by the part of the specimen that is coherent with the protologue, in this case, the flowering branch. The isolectotype in NY indicates a collection number 288, but this same number is also used in a 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FF95FFE93A190AAD449EBA9A" box="[834,944,411,437]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="27" pageNumber="254" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Moraceae</taxonomicName>
and should be ignored.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBEABDD9FF95FFE939E60A88441BB9D7" pageId="27" pageNumber="254" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FF95FFE939E60A88455BB9A3" blockId="27.[136,1452,158,977]" pageId="27" pageNumber="254">
<emphasis id="91843240FF95FFE939E60A8846D9BAF7" bold="true" box="[189,503,446,472]" pageId="27" pageNumber="254">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FF95FFE93B480A884443BAF7" authorityName="Poeppig &amp; Endlicher" authorityYear="1845" box="[531,877,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="27" pageNumber="254" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="paniculatum">
<emphasis id="91843240FF95FFE93B480A884443BAF7" box="[531,877,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="254">Stryphnodendron paniculatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to the Brazilian Amazon, occurring along rivers in areas of non-flooded 
<emphasis id="91843240FF95FFE93B7B0AD545B4BAD3" box="[544,666,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="254">terra firme</emphasis>
forests in 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF95FFE93A4B0AD444AEBAD3" box="[784,896,482,508]" country="Brazil" name="Rondonia" pageId="27" pageNumber="254">Rondônia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF95FFE93AD20AD444D1BAD3" box="[905,1023,482,508]" country="Venezuela" name="Amazonas" pageId="27" pageNumber="254">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF95FFE93D6D0AD44346BAD3" box="[1078,1128,482,508]" country="Suriname" name="Para" pageId="27" pageNumber="254">Pará</collectingRegion>
states. The species is mostly distributed along the Solimões and 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF95FFE93B48093045A7B90F" box="[531,649,518,544]" country="Venezuela" name="Amazonas" pageId="27" pageNumber="254">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
rivers and occupies the Amazonian territory in its central portion in the east-west direction. It grows in the phytogeographic provinces of Southeast, Western Solimões-Amazônia, Manaus, Xingu-Madeira in the state of 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF95FFE9388D09784562B947" box="[470,588,590,616]" country="Venezuela" name="Amazonas" pageId="27" pageNumber="254">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
(Central-Western Amazon) and rarely in the provinces of Jarí-Trombetas and Atlantic-Coastal (Central-Eastern Amazon).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FF95FFE939E609A0441BB9D7" blockId="27.[136,1452,158,977]" pageId="27" pageNumber="254">
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FF95FFE939E609A0453CB99F" authorityName="Poeppig &amp; Endlicher" authorityYear="1845" box="[189,530,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="27" pageNumber="254" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="paniculatum">
<emphasis id="91843240FF95FFE939E609A0453CB99F" box="[189,530,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="254">Stryphnodendron paniculatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is reported by 
<bibRefCitation id="C76193A3FF95FFE93BE109A044B0B99F" author="Ribeiro, J. E. L. S. &amp; Hopkins, M. J. G. &amp; Vicentini, A. &amp; Sothers, C. A. &amp; Costa, M. A. S. &amp; Brito, J. M. &amp; Souza, M. A. D. &amp; Martins, L. H. &amp; Lohmann, L. G. &amp; Assuncao, P. A. &amp; Pereira, E. C. &amp; Silva, C. F. &amp; Mesquita, M. R. &amp; Procopio, L. C." box="[698,926,662,688]" pageId="27" pageNumber="254" refId="ref44066" refString="Ribeiro, J. E. L. S., Hopkins, M. J. G., Vicentini, A., Sothers, C. A., Costa, M. A. S., Brito, J. M., Souza, M. A. D., Martins, L. H., Lohmann, L. G., Assuncao, P. A., Pereira, E. C., Silva, C. F., Mesquita, M. R. &amp; Procopio, L. C. (1999) Flora da Reserva Ducke. Guia de identificacao das plantas vasculares de uma floresta de terra firme na Amazonia Central. Manaus: INPA-DFID, 800 pp." type="book" year="1999">
Ribeiro 
<emphasis id="91843240FF95FFE93A4E09A14463B99F" box="[789,845,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="254">et al.</emphasis>
(1999)
</bibRefCitation>
as a species with rare occurrence in the Ducke Forest Reserve (Manaus, 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF95FFE938FF098C4531B9FB" box="[420,543,698,724]" country="Venezuela" name="Amazonas" pageId="27" pageNumber="254">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
), in areas of plateau forest (higher areas with well drained clayey soil and poor in nutrients). It´s abundance in the remaining areas is unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBEABDD9FF95FFE939E60834466AB84B" pageId="27" pageNumber="254" type="description">
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FF95FFE939E608344349B832" blockId="27.[136,1452,158,977]" box="[189,1127,770,797]" pageId="27" pageNumber="254">
